#week-title("Three", "Setting the First Cohobation")

=== Core Teaching

This week, set up your first cohobation. Place your calcined Salt in a clean flask.
Slowly pour your extracted essence over it until the Salt is fully submerged.
Seal the flask tightly (using parafilm to prevent leaks) and place it in a source
of gentle, sustained warmth.

*Critical Diagnostic:* A genuine preparation should, when warm and soft, flow like
wax and penetrate other bodies. If it is dry, brittle, and inert, the natural
moisture has been lost through overheating. Review the Four Common Errors from
Month 3 if this occurs.

=== Topics This Week

- Practical setup: Salt and Essence reunion
- Monitoring for leaks (the "smell test")
- Observing color changes in the liquid as it digests
- Diagnostic check: Wax-like flow when warm

#inner-work[
  *The Marriage of Opposites*

  Cohobation is a localized enactment of a cosmic theme: the volatile (spirit/soul)
  descends into the fixed (body), and the fixed rises to meet it.

  Sit with your sealed cohobation flask for five minutes each day. Observe the
  interface between the Salt and the Essence. Contemplate the "marriage" occurring
  within the glass. Record your observations in your lab journal.
]

